    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Folk shawm of Spain, with conical bore. The same instrument is also known as a bolingozo in the Basque region.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000048177/Marcuse, Musical Instruments (1964)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093511/Library of Congress Authorities online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>西班牙民間雙簧管，具圓錐形內管。在巴斯克地區(Basque region)亦被稱為波鈴歌佐(bolingozo)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
